Typography

Slab serif typefaces are often considered a sub-set of Serif Fonts and also have the same little "feet" at the ends of each character. They also establish a classic and traditional look but are a lot bolder and more confident. Slab serif fonts are best suited for companies who want to make a strong impression in their industry and aren't afraid to show it.
